H0.text: Lucrezia, Cesare, and Rodrigo were part of what papal family. Medici

H1.text: Lucrezia, Cesare, and Rodrigo were part of what papal family. Este

H2.text: Lucrezia, Cesare, and Rodrigo were part of what papal family. Farnese

H3.text: Lucrezia, Cesare, and Rodrigo were part of what papal family. Borgia

A4.text: The Borgias became prominent in ecclesiastical and political affairs in the 15th and 16th centuries, producing two popes: Alfons de Borja, who ruled as Pope Callixtus III during 1455–1458, and his nephew Rodrigo Lanzol Borgia, as Pope Alexander VI, during 1492–1503.

A5.text: Lucrezia was born in Subiaco, Italy to Cardinal Rodrigo Borgia and Roman mistress Vannozza dei Catanei.
